issue_title: Added Tabs.setSwipeOnYAxis(...) method to set the swipe on Y-Axis.
issue_comments: [['Shai Almog', 'Mon Nov 22 02:20:15 2021', " I have two small nitpicks with the code The variable is swipeX while the method is swipeY I suggest making the method swipe X and setting it to false would do what you want This would also fix the second problem Right now you can't toggle this back and forth because of the if statement in that method By just exposing the variable this should be solved You would also need to add an isSwipeX method for consistency"]]
issue_words: This addition follows our discussion https new reddit com r cn comments quq yo realize a set of containers that are browsable To test the code you can try this example https gist github com jsfan c b c e c dae The changes I've made should have no impact on the existing code or so I think I have followed as much as possible the logic of the pre existing code For the moment I have only tried in the Simulator I have seen a minor pre existing bug it does not depend on my modifications It occurs only if the tabs have a margin in such a case for a fraction of a second the Motion moves the incoming tab entirely to the left during the swipe thus ignoring the margin This bug is almost undetectable in a move along the X axis However if the swipe is along the Y axis the bug becomes visible It's a minor problem that I don't know how to fix for the moment the workaround is to have a zero margin as in the above linked sample code

issue_title: Steps to reproduce the wizard issues consistently
issue_comments: [['Steve Hannah', 'Thu Nov  4 12:16:44 2021', ' I have tried the steps you described and cannot reproduce Is it possible that your codenameone settings properties file is pointing to a different iOS certificate or provisioning profile than you expect']]
issue_words: Steps to reproduce the wizard issues consistently I tried several times Generate a new project with https start codenameone com with a new never used package name Follow README adoc instructions according to your IDE I use Netbeans Run Maven Update Codename One Run Maven Open Control Center Follow the iOS Certificate Wizard remember to enable Push You receive the Push instructions by email Send iOS Debug build It fails with the error Provisioning profile does not have Push enabled Either set the ios includePush build hint to false or generate a new provisioning profile with Push enabled Rerun the Wizard with Push enabled You receive the Push instructions again by email Send an iOS Debug build It fails again but with a different error The provided provisioning profile and certificate do not match Please ensure that the provisioning profile you provide was generated using the certificate that you provide To skip validation you may add the ios validateProvisioningProfile false build hint Tested both on Linux and MacOS with Netbeans

issue_title: unnecessary bloat in IOS source codfe
issue_comments: [['Steve Hannah', 'Mon Nov  1 13:26:40 2021', ' Thanks for spotting this I have committed a fix that will be part of the next update on Friday']]
issue_words: Class ArimaaViewer extends commonCanvas In the m and h files corresponding to ArimaaViewer I find this JAVA BOOLEAN get field arimaa ArimaaViewer useAuxSliders JAVA OBJECT cn T return struct obj arimaa ArimaaViewer cn T online game commonCanvas useAuxSliders void set field arimaa ArimaaViewer useAuxSliders CODENAME ONE THREAD STATE JAVA BOOLEAN cn Val JAVA OBJECT cn T struct obj arimaa ArimaaViewer cn T online game commonCanvas useAuxSliders cn Val The problem is that the variable useAuxSliders is a private variable of commonCanvas and can't legally be used by ArimaaViewer No big deal from the viewpoint of legality since code to call it won't ever be generated by Java The problem is the code bloat caused by including all these meaningless getters and setters in class ArimaaViewer They still have to be compiled and probably post compilation sent to oblivion which takes time This kind of thing is a major contributor to my build times for IOS class commonCanvas has many private instance variables and is subclassed or more times

issue_title: Database/Cursor cleanup doesn't actually work, leading to iOS crash when garbage collector runs
issue_comments: [['Rochana Sawatzky', 'Tue Nov  2 18:37:50 2021', " Is there anything I can do to have this looked at It's causing constant crashing for my ios app users if they have the app open for longer than a minute or two If I could create a test function that caused it would that help It didn't happen as much when I originally published my app but every time I add more functionality it gets worse because the app has more data to look at"]]
issue_words: Describe the bug My app crashes after being used for a while on iOS I thought it was a memory issue and ran memory profiling but there was lots of free memory I use a Database in my app and I believe that the problem is that the database cursor cleanup doesn't actually work leading to iOS crash when garbage collector runs I thought that maybe opening closing the database was causing the problem so I changed my code to just try opening the database once and keeping it open but then I got this message WARNING DB Cursor was released by the GC without being closed first This might cause crashes on iOS WARNING Database object was released by the GC without being closed first This might cause crashes on iOS So I deployed this code not closing the database cursor to my iPad and found that it crashed after the same amount of navigation I'm pretty sure that what's happening is despite me cleaning up the Database and Cursor in a finally block after doing my query it's not getting properly closed I have tried Util cleanup db cur and just close in a try catch and neither works To Reproduce Steps to reproduce the behavior Do a Database query using a Cursor Attempt to close that using Util cleanup db Util cleanup cur Create enough memory overhead in the app to get the garbage collector to run App crashes stops responding correctly when trying to access database

issue_title: Permission request text is not displayed the first time the permission requested
issue_comments: [['Steve Hannah', 'Thu Sep  9 12:51:34 2021', " This fix will be part of tomorrow's update"]]
issue_words: Describe the bug The https www codenameone com blog switching on android marshmallow permission prompts html says When permission is requested a user will be seamlessly prompted warned we have builtin text to control such prompts but you might want to customize the text You can customize permission text via the Display properties This doesn't work with ACCESS FINE LOCATION The custom message is shown only after user denied the permission and then requested it again It has Don't ask and Ask again buttons so it seems like the dialog is suppose to be shown only after the user declined the permission the first time it was asked image https user images githubusercontent com a c e eb bd dc d bdab png First time it's requested no dialog boxes are shown According to the blog I assumed that the Display properties can customize the text at the moment permission is requested including the first request To Reproduce Steps to reproduce the behavior Follow https www codenameone com blog switching on android marshmallow permission prompts html Add Display getInstance setProperty android permission ACCESS FINE LOCATION Location required custom string from init into your init Object context method Build the app open it and try to do something that will request location Expected behavior Show Location required custom string from init in a Dialog OS Android Smartphone please complete the following information Device Moto g play OS Android API

issue_title: Add CEF as part of the JavaSE Local build
issue_comments: [['Javier Anton', 'Thu Jul  8 22:45:57 2021', " The announcement of Windows incorporating native android apps together with new macs running arm code will likely render the requirement for a JavaSE build obsolete Not sure how soon that will happen but basically I'm not too fussed about needing chromium in JavaSE anymore Feel free to reopen if this becomes of interest"]]
issue_words: Unlike the Simulator local JavaSE builds use JavaFX instead of CEF Ideally now that CEF is an option JavaSE builds should have the option to use it instead of relying on JavaFX Perhaps a build hint can determine whether JavaFX or CEF is used If the build process can't automatically copy the CEF libraries to output manual copy would be ok

issue_comments: [['Steve Hannah', 'Fri May 21 20:49:44 2021', ' Fixed in git Will be part of next update']]
issue_words: It's a small problem that's easy to notice but those who aren't careful are likely to get it wrong In the readme txt file inside the iosCerts folder generated via your wizard there is Development Push Certificate URL https codename one push certificates s amazonaws com xxx ProductionPushxxx p Development Push Certificate Password 'xxx' Production Push Certificate URL https codename one push certificates s amazonaws com xxx DevelopmentPushxxx p Production Push Certificate Password 'xxx' As you can see Production and Development urls are inverted I don't know if the same error is in the email because I didn't receive the email or I absent mindedly deleted it

issue_title: Can't run Simulator when JavaSE native interface code references custom Java classes in JavaSE folder
issue_words: When a maven project's JavaSE folder contains any custom java class AND the JavaSE native interface uses that custom class running the Simulator results in a package x does not exist error thrown from the place where the native interface uses that custom class and the simulator doesn't start

issue_title: iOS Sqlite Issue
issue_comments: [['Shai Almog', 'Fri Jun  4 17:23:46 2021', ' Based on this https stackoverflow com questions store huge data in sqlite I would suggest having a transaction in place instead of sleeping']]
issue_words: Sqlite on iOS C C sqlite presents the following problem when transactions are executed in rapid succession a of them gets execute twice In the past it has been noted that Sqlite is thread sensitive But I have now tested this thoroughly and have found that the issue is not only that sqlite is thread sensitive in this particular instance it also is that it can't handle multiple consecutive calls gracefully even when they are made from the same thread To test this I wrapped my calls in an EasyThread to make sure we don't actually have a threading issue and called queries in a for loop like so function and vars definition EasyThread dbTasks EasyThread start DBTasks public void createNewTestTable transaction CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS TEST TEST Id uuid PRIMARY KEY UNIQUE executeTransaction transaction public void insertIntoTestTable String transaction INSERT INTO TEST TEST Id VALUES X' getRandomHexBlob ' this executeTransaction transaction public String getRandomHexBlob Random r new Random StringBuffer sb new StringBuffer while sb length sb append Integer toHexString r nextInt return sb toString substring toUpperCase public Boolean executeTransaction String query returns success error return dbTasks run try db execute query this example doesn't show how to initialize the db variable please do that elsewhere if getPlatformName equals ios pauseForSafety return true catch Exception ex log a duplicate here return false public long lastTimeDBAccessed public void pauseForSafety try if System currentTimeMillis lastTimeDBAccessed if last transaction was within previous ms wait ms Thread sleep lastTimeDBAccessed System currentTimeMillis catch Exception ex log if desired test method content createNewTestTable for int i i i insertIntoTestTable The above code includes code that ensures that no transaction is ever executed within ms of each other This prevents the duplicate transaction problem on iOS But if the call to pauseForSafety is removed and the exception in executeTransaction is logged it will be seen that multiple violation of UNIQUE Id errors are thrown I am opening this issue so that we are aware of this and perhaps can find a solution that doesn't require manually distancing each transaction ms from each other This can't be completely safe Could it be that there is a newer version of sqlite that perhaps doesn't have this problem Is there something in CN 's implementation that triggers this Interestingly the duplicates seem to also increase in number when the EDT is blocked doing other things If for example we call from threads like so getInstance createNewTestTable Runnable oneThreadExe for int i i i SqlLite getInstance insertIntoTestTable Display getInstance callSerially Utils getInstance showDialogNoBlock Info Done Thread execThread Display getInstance createThread oneThreadExe execThread start Thread execThread Display getInstance createThread oneThreadExe execThread start No duplicates will be found as long as we space transactions ms from each other If however we call from one thread and then from the EDT at the same time no length of pause will be enough to prevent duplicates createNewTestTable Runnable oneThreadExe for int i i i SqlLite getInstance insertIntoTestTable Display getInstance callSerially Utils getInstance showDialogNoBlock Info Done Thread execThread Display getInstance createThread oneThreadExe execThread start oneThreadExe run calling from EDT This is not a huge deal btw Just writing it down in case it becomes of interest

issue_title: iOS build issue
issue_comments: [['Javier Anton', 'Sat May  8 15:55:36 2021', ' The solution to this problem consists in swapping the key UIBackgroundModes key array string remote notification string array in ios plistInject with ios background modes remote notification']]
issue_words: Server error Exception java io IOException You cannot use both ios background modes build hint and use UIBackgroundModes in the ios plistInject build hint Choose one or the other I don't use ios background modes build hint in my project but I do use key UIBackgroundModes key array string remote notification string array in my ios plistInject build hint I use that plist hint because I implement my own push mechanism I can always add it to the source project which I always modify anyway but perhaps the build process could be improved to allow the plist one without throwing an error This has started happening recently I assume because of the new available Push for everyone

issue_title: Maven doesn't support hotreload
issue_comments: [['Steve Hannah', 'Fri May  7 11:29:33 2021', " I added that message I was having difficulty getting IntelliJ's hot reload to work with Maven and frankly the hot reload isn't very good anyways it's only good for changing small bits of code doesn't support adding new methods and classes etc so I did a bit of research on alternatives and found that HotswapAgent https github com HotswapProjects HotswapAgent works great so I added hot reload based on HotswapAgent support directly into the simulator The simulator now watches the source directories for changes and will trigger a full maven re compile when changes are detected The Hotswap agent pulls in the changes seamlessly This works even if you add remove classes and methods I sometimes need to do a fresh restart of the simulator but for the most part this works well So far I have been testing with just using the DEVM JDK https github com TravaOpenJDK trava jdk dcevm releases which includes the hotswap agent and just adding the XX HotswapAgent core to the VM options in the IntelliJ settings I'm going to explore making it more seamless so that users don't need to use any particular VM This is still experimental but very promising Links Hotswap Agent https github com HotswapProjects HotswapAgent DEVM JDK with Hotswap Agent https github com TravaOpenJDK trava jdk dcevm releases Hotswap Agent IntelliJ plugin https github com dmitry zhuravlev hotswap agent intellij plugin I have not tried this but I will be looking into its source as a reference I have been using this setup for the development of the Twitter UI kit and it has been wonderful I can make changes throughout the codebase and instantly second delay see the results in my UI without having to restart the simulator"]]
issue_words: Open Maven project in intellij and debug on simulator Select the Run Debugging Actions Reload Changed Classes menu option from Intellij You get the following printout Hotswap Agent not detected To enable enhanced live class reloading feature run with DCEVM JDK and add XX HotswapAgent core to the VM options

issue_title: Android local build bug?
issue_words: Using plugin When building an Android local build the resulting proguard cfg file is missing the following line keepclassmembers class com zooz android lib I have to add it manually because it does include the following next lines and so the syntax breaks It includes proguard cfg public I have to change it to keepclassmembers class com zooz android lib public I saw that it was missing that line by comparing the local build's file to the one from the build sever's sources

issue_title: Build process unnecessarily adds `android:name="androidx.multidex.MultiDexApplication"` to the manifest's `<application` block when `android.multidex=true`
issue_comments: [['Javier Anton', 'Tue Apr 20 21:40:00 2021', " I just realized that the reason why dex is needed in local builds is that it isn't obfuscating with ProGuard by default"]]
issue_words: In most cases it won't cause any problems But in the case where we have a custom Android class that manages the application's lifecycle this will disrupt and throw an error when building with the build hint android multidex true That is because there will then be android name properties within the application Now when building through the build server it isn't necessary to use the build hint android multidex true But when building locally it is So can we prevent this unnecessary bit from being added to avoid the manual step of removing this image https user images githubusercontent com a f a a eb ab a f png

issue_title: Some issues with the CN1 Maven support
issue_comments: [['Steve Hannah', 'Tue Apr 13 19:20:03 2021', " Normally a Kotlin project accepts a mix of Java and Kotlin files With the Ant support I could mix kt and java files in the same project and everything worked fine With this new Maven support when I mix these two file formats in a kotlin project the first run goes fine and everything displays fine but when I make changes to the java file and re executes the code the simulator starts but the modifications are not applied Any modification that is done after the first execution in the java file is not applied at all With Ant this problem was not present What is the cause I can't reproduce this Steps I used Created Bare bones kotlin project using initializr Added Java class package ca weblite kotlintest public class HelloJ public String getString return hello Added button in Kotlin class that uses this class E g val btn Button Click Me btn addActionListener Log p HelloJ getString hi add btn Run in simulator Click button Prints hello Change getString method to return hello Run in simulator Click button Prints hello now With the previous Ant build system we can see methods documentation in the popup in the IDE With Maven this documentation is no longer displayed Can you fix that please I can't reproduce this E g image https user images githubusercontent com bf a c eb e a a png In the Codename One Maven developer guide you show how to create CN maven project via the command line and Codename One initializer Can you also add in the documentation how to do it directly via the IDE without going through the two previous options You should be able to just adapt the instructions that you see for command line Note the parameters that you need to add in whatever IDE you use"]]
issue_words: Hello I have a few things to report about Maven support Normally a Kotlin project accepts a mix of Java and Kotlin files With the Ant support I could mix kt and java files in the same project and everything worked fine With this new Maven support when I mix these two file formats in a kotlin project the first run goes fine and everything displays fine but when I make changes to the java file and re executes the code the simulator starts but the modifications are not applied Any modification that is done after the first execution in the java file is not applied at all With Ant this problem was not present What is the cause With the previous Ant build system we can see methods documentation in the popup in the IDE With Maven this documentation is no longer displayed Can you fix that please In the Codename One Maven developer guide you show how to create CN maven project via the command line and Codename One initializer Can you also add in the documentation how to do it directly via the IDE without going through the two previous options Thanks

issue_words: After the last update an endless ERROR log is shown in the console ERROR network service instance impl cc Network service crashed restarting service ERROR network service instance impl cc Network service crashed restarting service ERROR network service instance impl cc Network service crashed restarting service ERROR network service instance impl cc Network service crashed restarting service ERROR network service instance impl cc Network service crashed restarting service It only shows when Google MapContainer is added to a form and it doesn't stop after navigating to another form It might be related to the CEF browser as this line shows once before the endless log INFO CONSOLE Uncaught TypeError getMapContainer fireMapChangeEvent is not a function source https cn app streams java Location loc getCurrentLocation final MapContainer map new MapContainer App GOOGLE API KEY map setShowMyLocation true map setRotateGestureEnabled false zoomTo map new Coord loc getLatitude loc getLongitude add CENTER map Edit This might also be happening on Android as well and it's affecting the BrowserComponent The browser stopped showing in both Sim and Android java BrowserComponent browser new BrowserComponent browser setURL Payment CHECKOUT URL params toString browser addBrowserNavigationCallback url System out println url if url contains payments success String query StringUtils split url Optional String paymentId Stream of query findLast if paymentId isPresent completeBooking previous booking CARD paymentId get else failureDialog show else if url contains payments cancel CustomDialog cancelDialog new CustomDialog Payment Cancelled Could not confirm your booking because your payment was cancelled If this was in error then be sure to mail us at App CONTACT EMAIL fontImage CANCEL CIRCLE Size LARGE ICON Color SECONDARY P Ok ev previous showBack cancelDialog show return true add CENTER browser

issue_title: Upcoming bug in Android WebView (currently found in Beta) that afectes CN1 apps hosting a BrowserComponent
issue_comments: [['Javier Anton', 'Wed Mar 17 08:07:32 2021', " shannah shai almog the guys at Chromium have isolated the cause to a specific commit in their branch https chromium googlesource com chromium src log One of these changes is making CN 's BrowserComponent not visible when its Form hits showBack"]]
issue_words: The bug isn't yet present in stable releases of Android Webview but has already made its way from Dev and Canary to Beta Basically a CN form that contains a BrowserComponent will lose its BrowserComponent when shown back Even though this happens when the Beta version of WebView is installed on Android it also stops happening if previous getContentPane revalidateWithAnimationSafety is called right after previous showBack However even with this fix the user is required to tap the screen to bring back the BrowserComponent to a visible state The beta version of Android System Webview can be installed from the Play store Once installed go to Settings Dev Options Webview Implementation and select the beta version installed Then test the error with the below code just call testMethod from anywhere public void testMethod Form previous Display getInstance getCurrent Form welcomeForm new Form Test new BorderLayout BrowserComponent tstBrowser new BrowserComponent tstBrowser setURL https www google com welcomeForm add BorderLayout CENTER tstBrowser welcomeForm getToolbar addMaterialCommandToRightBar GO FORWARD FontImage MATERIAL ARROW FORWARD ee testMethod welcomeForm show public void testMethod Form previous Display getInstance getCurrent Form welcomeForm new Form Test new BorderLayout welcomeForm getToolbar addMaterialCommandToLeftBar ShowBack FontImage MATERIAL ARROW BACK ee previous showBack welcomeForm show Here is a video of the error using the above code in action https user images githubusercontent com c ac eb f a c e c mp I filed an issue with Chromium but then asked to close it because it seems like the error is on CN 's side https bugs chromium org p chromium issues detail id
